1072
00:42:12,360 --> 00:42:13,910
and check if there's any swelling.

1073
00:42:14,540 --> 00:42:15,430
If not,

1074
00:42:15,430 --> 00:42:16,690
you can hold the area

1075
00:42:16,690 --> 00:42:17,990
under cool running water,

1076
00:42:18,200 --> 00:42:19,580
or soak it in cool water

1077
00:42:19,580 --> 00:42:20,590
until it doesn't hurt.

1078
00:42:20,590 --> 00:42:22,570
If there're already large areas

1079
00:42:22,570 --> 00:42:24,120
of burns on the patient's skin,

1080
00:42:25,040 --> 00:42:25,800
first,

1081
00:42:25,800 --> 00:42:27,440
the patient should lie down quickly.

1082
00:42:27,440 --> 00:42:28,910
Lift the wound

1083
00:42:29,450 --> 00:42:31,510
and check if there are any other hidden wounds.

1084
00:42:31,970 --> 00:42:33,610
If the conditions are convenient,

1085
00:42:33,610 --> 00:42:35,460
you can apply thick disinfectant dressings

1086
00:42:35,460 --> 00:42:37,220
to the surface of the wounds

1087
00:42:37,560 --> 00:42:38,480
for protection.

1088
00:42:38,740 --> 00:42:40,420
Don't try to remove

1089
00:42:40,420 --> 00:42:42,090
